text: Ames State Forest is in Henniker, New Hampshire. It covers . It was established after Flora Ames, a resident of Henniker, donated about 15 acres to the state for reforestation. Keyser Pond Campground on Keyser Pond and Craney Hill State Forest are nearby. ==See also== *List of New Hampshire state forests ==References== Category:Landforms of Merrimack County, New Hampshire Category:New Hampshire state forests
